      • setRemoteConstrTypes

        public RemoteDescriptor.Builder setRemoteConstrTypes(java.lang.Class<?>... remoteConstrTypes)
        Sets the remote constructor types of the EspressoRemoteMessage associated with this RemoteDescriptor.

        The types passed to this method will be used to reflectively infer the remote message constructor.

        By default the instanceType is used as remote message constructor. Only set custom remote constructor types, when the remote message constructor takes a superclass or interface, implemented by the instance type. Don't call this method when using GenericRemoteMessage.

        Parameters:
        remoteConstrTypes -
        Returns:
        fluent builder interface

Generated javadoc for the new package structure to make it clearer which packages are bundled with the Android operating system, and which are packaged with your app's APK. Going forward, the android.* package hierarchy will be reserved for Android packages that ship with the operating system; other packages will be issued in the new androidx.* package hiearchy.
